---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Research" description="Papers, code, and datasets from the Oxford LLMs research programme.">

  <!-- ── Hero ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="hero-manuscript">
    <div class="hero-ms-inner">
      <aside class="hero-ms-rail">
        <span class="rail-label">Contents</span>
        <ol class="rail-toc">
          <li>
            <a href="#themes">
              <span class="t-num">01</span>
              <span class="t-name">Themes</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#open">
              <span class="t-num">02</span>
              <span class="t-name">Open</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <div class="rail-foot">
          <span>Open source</span>
          <span>Oxford</span>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="hero-ms-content">
        <p class="eyebrow-v3">Research</p>
        <h1 class="hero-title h-display" style="margin: 16px 0 24px;">
          Methods for LLMs<br>in social science.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          Synthetic data generation, opinion prediction, annotator disagreement, and model evaluation.
          Code and datasets are open source on GitHub and Hugging Face.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 01 Themes ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker section-tinted-v3" id="themes">
    <span class="section-number">§ 01 · Themes</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Research themes</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">What we work on, and why.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          Three intertwined questions sit underneath most of what we publish,
          and most of what we teach.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px;"
           class="reveal-stagger">

        <article class="fb">
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:10px">Synthetic data</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0; font-size:14px;">
            Can LLMs generate respondent panels that pass standard quality checks?
            When they do not, where do they fail, and can we measure it before we use them?
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="fb">
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:10px">Opinion prediction</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0; font-size:14px;">
            How well do open-weights models recover real survey responses across languages,
            age cohorts, and political contexts, and what drives the gaps?
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="fb">
          <span class="rule-soft"></span>
          <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin-bottom:10px">Evaluation</h3>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0; font-size:14px;">
            Building eval sets that survive contamination, treating annotator disagreement
            as a measurement rather than a problem, and reporting confidence honestly.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 02 Open ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker" id="open"
           style="padding-bottom: clamp(56px, 7vw, 88px);">
    <span class="section-number">§ 02 · Open</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Open by default</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">Code on GitHub.<br>Weights on Hugging Face.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          Replication code ships with the paper, not six months after. Model checkpoints
          are released under permissive licences whenever we control the training data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;"
           class="reveal-stagger">

        <a class="fb" href="https://github.com/Oxford-LLMs-Research"
           target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="display:block;">
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:10px;">
            <img src="/img/icons/github-mark.svg" alt="" style="width:24px; height:24px; opacity:0.85;">
            <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin:0;">Oxford-LLMs-Research</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0 0 12px; font-size:14px;">
            Code and evaluation tooling for our research projects, including harnesses
            for running LLMs at survey scale. All repositories are public.
          </p>
          <span class="btn-link-v3">Open on GitHub <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
        </a>

        <a class="fb" href="https://huggingface.co/oxford-llms"
           target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="display:block;">
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:10px;">
            <img src="/img/icons/hf-logo.svg" alt="" style="width:24px; height:24px;">
            <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin:0;">oxford-llms</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0 0 12px; font-size:14px;">
            Model checkpoints and datasets from our research on synthetic data
            generation and opinion prediction.
          </p>
          <span class="btn-link-v3">Open on Hugging Face <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
